author: brane
msg: Follow-up to r1576277: JavaHL's current status editor implementation
relies on seeing a file with (apparently) new contents of a file to
Open the delta target file with the open-on-close flag enabled,
so that the file does get created even if there is no text delta
in the editor drive; but it also gets closed immediately, so that
the handle does not stay in use indefinitely.
